<h1>Welcome!</h1>
<p>This is Your Guide to Cubing. <br> I will run through some basic algorithms to get you started and some top tips.</p>
<h2><u>Choice of Cube</u></h2>
<p>To get started with, you won't need a very good cube, so a cheap one will do. Then again, you need one that is sort of decent that isn't too stiff to move.</p>
<p>Quick Side Note: I am referring to a 3x3x3 cube, as that's the one most people are fascinated by at first.</p>
